s industry\r\n\r\n<!--.info-->&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href=\"/services/procurement\">Procurement Services</a></h3>\r\nWe handle procurement and standardization services for projects ….blah blah blah\r\n\r\n<!--.info-->&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href=\"/services/manpower-development\">Manpower Development</a></h3>\r\nOur team of experts train your staff in industry best practices and standards for optimal operations.\r\n\r\n<!--.info-->','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2016-07-18 15:53:49','2016-07-18 15:53:49','',4,'http://bolag.dev/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2016-07-18 15:58:56','2016-07-18 15:58:56','<strong> DESIGN, CONSTRUCTION, AND OPERATION OF A LIQUEFIED PETROLEUM GAS (LPG) PLANT</strong>\r\nOAKJARS COMPANY LIMITED commissioned Bolag Resources Limited to act as the project manager for the Design, Construction, and Operation of a Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG) Plant at Ibafo, Ogun State Nigeria\r\n<strong>\r\nSCOPE OF WORK</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Advise the Client on Liquefied Petroleum Gas Plant Construction and Operations</li>\r\n 	<li>Advise the client on all Regulatory matters which include packaging all statutory requirements for the approval of the Liquefied Petroleum Gas Plant, the regulatory bodies include the Department of Petroleum Resources, Physical and Urban Planning Authority, Divisional Police, and Fire Services</li>\r\n 	<li>Monitor the Environmental Impact Assessment Studies</li>\r\n 	<li>Supervise the construction activities of the contractors to ensure that the plant is constructed as per approved drawings and that the appropriate specification and standards are met</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>PROGRESS REPORT</strong>\r\n<strong>Environmental Impact Assessment Studies</strong>\r\nBolag Resources Ltd monitored and ensured that the report of Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA) Studies is out no longer than when needed and also monitored the approval of the EIA report in the Department of Petroleum Resources.\r\n<strong>Detailed Engineering Design</strong>\r\nDetailed Engineering Design of the LPG Plant is being handled by Akindele Adeyemo &amp; Co while Bolag Resources Limited reviewed the design to ensure compliance with all provisions of the approved guidelines for the Design, Construction, and Operating the LPG filling Plant.\r\n<strong>Physical and Urban Planning Approval</strong>\r\nThe Design Drawings were submitted to the Ogun State Physical and Urban Planning Authority and approval was given which confirmed sitting of LPG Plant at the site in Ibafo, Ogun State.\r\n<strong>Police Report</strong>\r\nThe Police Report has been obtained which confirmed sitting of the LPG Plant at the said site will not constitute traffic hazard.\r\n<strong>Fire Report</strong>\r\nThe Fire Report has been obtained from the Ogun State Fire Services which confirmed sitting of the LPG Plant at the said site will not constitute Fire hazard to the immediate and beyond environs, and that arrangement for fire prevention and containment of fire are adequately addressed.\r\n<strong>Approval to Construct (ATC) the LPG Plant by the Department of Petroleum Resources</strong>\r\nBolag Resources Limited coordinated and monitored the activities of the regulatory agencies and contractors. The company has been following up the processing approval to construct the LPG with Department of Petroleum Resources\r\n<strong>Construction Works</strong>\r\nBolag Resources Ltd has been supervising the construction works at the site, through site inspection, periodic meetings with the contractor and the site engineer to ensure that the plant is constructed as per approved design and that all the facilities in place meet the requirement of DPR.\r\nFacilities under construction includes: The main office, a storey building, Generator House, Security Building and filling platform. The borehole has been completed while the 55metric ton storage tank with the ancillary items are been installed.','Oakjars Company Limited','DESIGN, CONSTRUCTION, AND OPERATION OF A LIQUEFIED PETROLEUM GAS (LPG) PLANT FOR\r\nOAKJARS COMPANY LIMITED','publish','closed','closed','','oakjars','','','2016-07-18 15:58:56','2016-07-18 15:58:56','',0,'http://bolag.dev/?post_type=projects&#038;p=36',0,'projects','',0),(37,1,'2016-07-21 11:46:25','2016-07-21 11:46:25','<h3 class=\"widget-title\">Our Services</h3>\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"/services/lpg\">Natural Gas Systems</a></h3>\nBolag Resources (BR) Oil &amp; Gas in partnership with RV Impianti – 3LP Gas Group of Italy delivers LPG &amp; Natural Gas products and services to the Nigeria market.\n\n<!--.info-->&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"/services/regulatory\">Regulatory Matters</a></h3>\nWe specialize in rendering services on regulatory matters for the Oil and Gas Industry in Nigeria\n\n<!--.info-->&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"/services/project-management/\">Project Management</a></h3>\nWe undertake construction project management for the Installation or modification of project facilities over a wide scope\n\n<!--.info-->&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"/services/design-optimization\">Plant Design &amp; Optimization</a></h3>\nWe handle engineering design, procurement, and construction of the facilities\n\n<!--.info-->&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"/services/environment\">Environmental Services</a></h3>\nWe provide relevant Environmental Impact Studies &amp; Assessments required for regulatory compliance.\n\n<!--.info-->&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"/services/training/\">Training</a></h3>\nOur team of experts train your staff in industry best practices and standards for optimal operations.\n\n<!--.info-->\n<h3 class=\"widget-title\">Natural Gas Systems</h3>\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"/services/turnkey-plants\">Turnkey Plants</a></h3>\nDesign, execution, installation and maintenance of L.P.G. – Natural gas plants for industrial use.\n\n<!--.info-->&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"/services/lpg-vaporizers\">LPG Vaporizers</a></h3>\nL.P.G. vaporizer represent a step ahead in the manufacturing of L.P.G. vaporization system